          <article class="this-site-cert-card">
            <p class="kicker">SC-900</p>
            <p>Zero Trust boundaries, telemetry-led control posture, and security principles in public-cloud workflows.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="this-site-cert-card">
            <p class="kicker">MS-102</p>
            <p>Identity governance patterns, role definition, and privileged admin guardrails.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="this-site-cert-card">
            <p class="kicker">MD-102</p>
            <p>Operational policy discipline, resilience planning, and recoverability thinking.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-tight">
      <div class="container reveal">
        <aside class="this-site-boundary-box" aria-label="Security disclosure boundary">
          <h2>Security disclosure boundary</h2>
          <p>This public case study documents control intent and architecture shape only.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>No account IDs, environment IDs, or policy IDs.</li>
            <li>No secret names, values, or token formats.</li>
            <li>No bucket/database identifiers or internal endpoint maps.</li>
            <li>No bypass logic, exception playbooks, or exploit narratives.</li>
          </ul>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>
